.TH "qla4xxx_sysfs_ddb_tgt_create" 9 "qla4xxx_sysfs_ddb_tgt_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
qla4xxx_sysfs_ddb_tgt_create \- Create sysfs entry for target
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" qla4xxx_sysfs_ddb_tgt_create
.BI "(struct scsi_qla_host *ha "  ","
.BI "struct dev_db_entry *fw_ddb_entry "  ","
.BI "uint16_t *idx "  ","
.BI "int user "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ha" 12
pointer to host
.IP "fw_ddb_entry" 12
flash ddb data
.IP "idx" 12
target index
.IP "user" 12
if set then this call is made from userland else from kernel
.SH "RETURN"
On sucess: QLA_SUCCESS
On failure: QLA_ERROR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This create separate sysfs entries for session and connection attributes of
the given fw ddb entry.
If this is invoked as a result of a userspace call then the entry is marked
as nonpersistent using flash_state field.
